---
---
<div class="qa-explainer-card">
  <div class="qa-explainer-header">
    <div class="header-icon-wrapper">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="header-svg"><path d="M12 22c5.523 0 10-4.477 10-10S17.523 2 12 2 2 6.477 2 12s4.477 10 10 10z"/><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/></svg>
    </div>
    <div>
      <span class="qa-badge">QA Pipeline Architecture</span>
      <h3>Platform Verification & Quality Assurance</h3>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <p class="qa-intro">
    Bluefin is validated as an <strong>image-based, atomic operating system</strong>. Rather than verifying single packages in isolation, our testing framework asserts the entire system state, ensuring immutability, update transitions, and seamless desktop environment integrations.
  </p>

  <div class="qa-grid">
    <!-- Grid Item 1: Execution Substrate -->
    <div class="qa-grid-item">
      <div class="item-header">
        <span class="step-num">01</span>
        <h5>Execution Substrate</h5>
      </div>
      <p>
        Jobs schedule on the homelab control-plane node (<code>ghost</code>). The pipeline provisions **ephemeral KubeVirt VMs** for full-virtualization tests or boots **parallel Wayland test containers** running Mutter with software LLVMpipe rendering.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Grid Item 2: BDD Automation -->
    <div class="qa-grid-item">
      <div class="item-header">
        <span class="step-num">02</span>
        <h5>BDD & Desktop Simulation</h5>
      </div>
      <p>
        Automated test runs trigger <strong>Python Behave</strong> BDD scenarios using **dogtail** to traverse the GNOME AT-SPI accessibility tree. This simulates real mouse moves, clicks, app launches, and desktop key combos.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Grid Item 3: System Contracts -->
    <div class="qa-grid-item">
      <div class="item-header">
        <span class="step-num">03</span>
        <h5>Immutability & Integrity</h5>
      </div>
      <p>
        The suites prove critical OS-level contracts: read-only <code>/usr</code> directories, writable <code>/var</code> paths, OCI image signatures, composefs integrity, flatpak portal boundaries, and rootless Podman execution.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h4 class="suites-heading">The 5 Core Test Suites</h4>
  <div class="suites-grid">
    <div class="suite-card">
      <div class="suite-card__header">
        <span class="suite-badge badge--smoke">smoke</span>
        <h6>GNOME Shell & Apps</h6>
      </div>
      <p>Verifies desktop startup, system extension configs, top-bar menus, and primary app wrappers (Ptyxis, Software Center).</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="suite-card">
      <div class="suite-card__header">
        <span class="suite-badge badge--common">common</span>
        <h6>Sandbox & Portals</h6>
      </div>
      <p>Asserts Flatpak sandbox portals, permission prompts, authorization overrides (polkit), and user space isolation boundaries.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="suite-card">
      <div class="suite-card__header">
        <span class="suite-badge badge--developer">developer</span>
        <h6>Dev Toolchains</h6>
      </div>
      <p>Validates Homebrew path setup, rootless Podman socket mappings, and developer command line tool configurations.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="suite-card">
      <div class="suite-card__header">
        <span class="suite-badge badge--software">software</span>
        <h6>Bazaar Flatpaks</h6>
      </div>
      <p>Tests the desktop application centers (Bazaar hub), Flatpak CLI actions, and local app metadata caching.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="suite-card">
      <div class="suite-card__header">
        <span class="suite-badge badge--system">system</span>
        <h6>Atomic OS Contract</h6>
      </div>
      <p>Ensures <code>bootc status</code> OCI transport validity, composefs signatures, staged upgrade queues, and rollbacks.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .qa-explainer-card {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.35) 0%, rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6) 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .qa-explainer-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .header-icon-wrapper {
    background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.2);
    color: #38bdf8;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .qa-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #38bdf8;
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }
  .qa-explainer-header h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #f8fafc;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .qa-intro {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #cbd5e1;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
    max-width: 850px;
  }
  .qa-intro strong {
    color: #38bdf8;
  }
  .qa-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(255px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .qa-grid-item {
    background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.25);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1rem;
  }
  .item-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .step-num {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #38bdf8;
    background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.1);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: monospace;
  }
  .qa-grid-item h5 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #cbd5e1;
  }
  .qa-grid-item p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: #94a3b8;
  }
  .suites-heading {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #94a3b8;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .suites-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .suite-card {
    background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.15);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0.85rem;
    transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;
  }
  .suite-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.25);
  }
  .suite-card__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .suite-card h6 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #cbd5e1;
  }
  .suite-badge {
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.05rem 0.3rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: monospace;
  }
  .badge--smoke { background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.1); color: #38bdf8; border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.15); }
  .badge--common { background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.1); color: #c084fc; border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.15); }
  .badge--developer { background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.1); color: #f472b6; border: 1px solid rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.15); }
  .badge--software { background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1); color: #4ade80; border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.15); }
  .badge--system { background: rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.1); color: #fb923c; border: 1px solid rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.15); }
  
  .suite-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: #64748b;
  }
</style>
